It's all in the delivery

text:
Apex is fun but I was also apprehensive about playing it the first time because of the squads mechanic. I prefer playing solo. But it really isn't all that bad and you can only get better by playing.

Only thing that would make it difficult for you are stream snipers. But that can be countered fairly easily by hiding the game on your stream while you queue.

Also, while it might make the game more difficult to win, if you really just want to run around at your own pace, you can queue up as a solo. You will be pitted up against other entire squads, but you won't have to worry about toxic teammates while you learn the game.

text:
Hi guys, I was the one to suggest the Hololive x MCC collab @ 3:46:40, and to be honest, it's been a thought ever since Gura wanted to do Minecraft minigames with the rest. Instead of a jump directly into the main competition, I think it would be fun for them to do it as a full Hololive collab (which has 48 members, including HoloCouncil) for 40 roster spots.
I think it'd be a fun collab suggestion for them to do akin to the Sports festival or the Mario Kart Tournament without the hassle of making the events in it. And by doing it as an inside Hololive collab, there'd be no real hard feelings among them if someone wins over another person. 
This is just a suggestion, and I do not want to hassle the HoloMems into doing anything they don't want to do. But I do hope that this can happen because I believe it'll be super fun for everyone involved. 
Cheers guys. Hope everyone is doing well. 
Amazing stream Gura, hope to see more of your Minecraft exploits in the near future. Good luck in the HoloEN x ID Mario Kart Tournament on Friday.

text:
Absolutely this.

It's better to have your own niche and bring in people (and keep them in) by filling in that vacuum, rather than trying to copycat everyone else and doing something you are totally not into. Especially since then you're competing for exactly the same audience, there are only so many people that are going to religiously watch every single APEX stream from every single VTuber - the rest are just going to go for their favs. Meanwhile, the people you could've brought in with your original niche will feel left out.

Plus, you are eventually going to run out of steam, trying to do something you don't enjoy and people will eventually pick up on that anyway, and also, it's going to be tiresome for you as well, which might bring the quality even further down.

Effort is important, but don't force yourself to do something you can't feel like doing at all. What ain't gonna work, ain't gonna work.
